<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900601-0038</DOCNO><DOCID>900601-0038.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   McDonnell Helicopter   Names Gunn President</HL><DATE>06/01/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B10</SO><CO>   MD WNEWS</CO><LP>   ST. LOUIS -- Thomas M. Gunn was named president ofMcDonnell Douglas Helicopter Co. He succeeds William P.Brown, who resigned last month in the wake of the company'spoor financial performance.   Mr. Gunn, 46 years old, was most recently vice presidentof program development at McDonnell Aircraft Co. Thehelicopter company, based in Mesa, Ariz., and the aircraftcompany, based in St. Louis, are units of McDonnell DouglasCorp.</LP><TEXT>   Mr. Gunn has held various marketing, strategic planningand government-affairs posts with other McDonnell Douglasaffiliates since joining the company in 1975. He also holds alaw degree. Mr. Brown, 57, has been a consultant to theparent company since he resigned.   Last year, the helicopter company had a $137 millionwrite-off mainly related to the Apache program, whichaccounted for about 80% of the company's revenue.</TEXT></DOC>